{
  "text": "Immunoblot and immunoprecipitation. For all experiments, cells were serum-starved, stimulated with 20 ng/mL of FGF1 and 10 \u03bcg/mL of heparin for 20 min (or as indicated). Cell lysis and immunoprecipitation were essentially performed as described previously [CITATION_1] . Proteins were separated on NuPAGE 4% to 12% Bis-Tris gels (Invitrogen) and transferred to polyvinylidene difluoride membranes (Millipore). Primary antibodies were incubated with the membrane overnight at 4\u00b0C. Membranes were washed and probed with InfraRedDye-conjugated secondary antibody, and then proteins were visualized using fluorescence detection on the Odyssey Infrared Imaging System (Li-cor).",
